verses.verse: O <S%H3212>come<s%>, let us <S%H7442>sing<s%> unto the <S%H3068>LORD<s%>: let us make a joyful <S%H7321>noise<s%> to the <S%H6697>rock<s%> of our <S%H3468>salvation<s%>.
Let us <S%H6923>come<s%> before his <S%H6440>presence<s%> with <S%H8426>thanksgiving<s%>, and make a joyful <S%H7321>noise<s%> unto him with <S%H2158>psalms<s%>. come: Heb. prevent his face
For the <S%H3068>LORD<s%> is a <S%H1419>great<s%> <S%H410>God<s%>, and a <S%H1419>great<s%> <S%H4428>King<s%> above all <S%H430>gods<s%>.

In his <S%H3027>hand<s%> are the deep <S%H4278>places<s%> of the <S%H776>earth<s%>: the <S%H8443>strength<s%> of the <S%H2022>hills<s%> is his also. In: Heb. In whose the strength: or, the heights of the hills are his
The <S%H3220>sea<s%> is his, and he <S%H6213>made<s%> it: and his <S%H3027>hands<s%> <S%H3335>formed<s%> the <S%H3006>dry<s%> land. The sea: Heb. Whose the sea is
O <S%H935>come<s%>, let us <S%H7812>worship<s%> and bow <S%H3766>down<s%>: let us <S%H1288>kneel<s%> <S%H6440>before<s%> the <S%H3068>LORD<s%> our <S%H6213>maker<s%>.

For he is our <S%H430>God<s%>; and we are the <S%H5971>people<s%> of his <S%H4830>pasture<s%>, and the <S%H6629>sheep<s%> of his <S%H3027>hand<s%>. To <S%H3117>day<s%> if ye will <S%H8085>hear<s%> his <S%H6963>voice<s%>,

<S%H7185>Harden<s%> not your <S%H3824>heart<s%>, as in the <S%H4808>provocation<s%>, and as in the <S%H3117>day<s%> of <S%H4531>temptation<s%> in the <S%H4057>wilderness<s%>: provocation: Heb. contention
When your <S%H1>fathers<s%> <S%H5254>tempted<s%> me, <S%H974>proved<s%> me, and <S%H7200>saw<s%> my <S%H6467>work<s%>.

<S%H705>Forty<s%> <S%H8141>years<s%> long was I <S%H6962>grieved<s%> with this <S%H1755>generation<s%>, and <S%H559>said<s%>, It is a <S%H5971>people<s%> that do <S%H8582>err<s%> in their <S%H3824>heart<s%>, and they have not <S%H3045>known<s%> my <S%H1870>ways<s%>:
Unto whom I <S%H7650>sware<s%> in my <S%H639>wrath<s%> that they should not <S%H935>enter<s%> into my <S%H4496>rest<s%>. that: Heb. if they enter into my rest
